Feature: Managing Parts List Positions

Background:
    GIVEN an assembly exists
        AND an item exists


Scenario Outline: Create New Parts List Position
    WHEN <role> creates a new parts list position for it
    THEN a new parts list position is <creation>

    Examples:
        | role                | creation      |
        | Engineering, public | generated     |
        | public              | not generated |


Scenario Outline: Change Parts List Position
    GIVEN a parts list position exists
    WHEN <role> changes this parts list position
    THEN the changed parts list position is <state>

    Examples:
        | role                | state     |
        | Engineering, public | saved     |
        | public              | not saved |


Scenario Outline: Copy Parts List Position
    GIVEN a parts list position exists
    WHEN <role> copies this parts list position
    THEN the parts list position is <action>

    Examples:
        | role                | action     |
        | Engineering, public | copied     |
        | public              | not copied |


Scenario Outline: Delete Parts List Position
    GIVEN a parts list position exists
    WHEN <role> deletes this parts list position
    THEN the parts list position is <action>

    Examples:
        | role                | action      |
        | Engineering, public | deleted     |
        | public              | not deleted |


Scenario Outline: Change State Of A Parts List Position
    GIVEN a parts list position exists
    WHEN <role> changes the state of this parts list position
        | FROM    | TO       |
        | Draft   | Review   |
    THEN the state of the parts list position is <state>

    Examples:
        | role                | state       |
        | Engineering, public | changed     |
        | public              | not changed |
